text: Maxim Focșa (born 21 April 1992) is a Moldavian football defender who plays for FC Sfântul Gheorghe Suruceni. ==Club career== In 2018, Focșa played for Maltese club Pembroke Athleta.Andrew Cohen sospiż tliet logħbiet, netnews.com.mt, 24 October 2018 ==International career== He made his debut for Moldova national football team on 17 November 2019 in a Euro 2020 qualifier against Iceland. ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1992 births Category:Sportspeople from Chișinău Category:Moldovan footballers Category:Moldova international footballers Category:Living people Category:FC Academia Chișinău players Category:FC Dinamo-Auto Tiraspol players Category:Valletta F.C. players Category:Balzan F.C. players Category:CS Petrocub Hîncești players Category:FC Zaria Bălți players Category:Pembroke Athleta F.C. players Category:FC Sfântul Gheorghe Suruceni players Category:Moldovan National Division players Category:Maltese Premier League players Category:Association football defenders Category:Moldovan expatriate footballers Category:Expatriate footballers in Malta
